WEBVTT

1
00:00:11.053 --> 00:00:12.763
[theme music playing]

2
00:00:14.000 --> 00:00:20.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

3
00:00:36.245 --> 00:00:38.247
[bats fluttering]

4
00:00:50.425 --> 00:00:52.427
[thunder crashes]

5
00:00:53.303 --> 00:00:55.305
[crows cawing]

6
00:01:00.227 --> 00:01:01.687
[lightning sizzles]

7
00:01:20.789 --> 00:01:22.791
[bats screeching]

8
00:01:46.148 --> 00:01:48.150
[crows cawing]

9
00:01:53.780 --> 00:01:54.823
[hinges creaking]

10
00:01:54.906 --> 00:01:57.200
[Dark Lord] <i>Your flesh is mortal.</i>

11
00:01:57.284 --> 00:02:02.831
<i>and in the end. all mortal flesh must die.</i>

12
00:02:03.999 --> 00:02:06.001
[vomits. groaning]

13
00:02:06.960 --> 00:02:08.170
[panting]

14
00:02:09.713 --> 00:02:11.548
[grunts softly]

15
00:02:12.466 --> 00:02:13.508
[flushes toilet]

16
00:02:17.763 --> 00:02:19.765
[indistinct chattering outside]

17
00:02:23.185 --> 00:02:24.519
[gasps] Ms. Wardwell!

18
00:02:24.603 --> 00:02:27.481
I'm so sorry. I didn't mean
to startle you. It's just I...

19
00:02:28.273 --> 00:02:31.610
It's just I saw you fleeing
Principal Hawthorne's office. and...

20
00:02:32.235 --> 00:02:35.280
[sighs] Oh. that man. that man.
that man. that man.

21
00:02:36.323 --> 00:02:38.784
[softly] Did he say something
just hideous to you?

22
00:02:38.867 --> 00:02:42.120
- He... He... Um...
- Want me to call your aunts?

23
00:02:42.204 --> 00:02:44.331
See if they can come pick you up.
take you home?

24
00:02:44.414 --> 00:02:47.501
No. No. No. no. I'm fine.
I just got light-headed. is all.

25
00:02:47.584 --> 00:02:49.294
Thank you. Ms. Wardwell.

26
00:02:53.924 --> 00:02:54.924
[door closes]

27
00:03:06.019 --> 00:03:07.688
[Ambrose] <i>Here's a question. Aunties.</i>

28
00:03:07.979 --> 00:03:11.233
How can one witch get
another witch's familiar to talk?

29
00:03:11.316 --> 00:03:14.569
You're not allowed a familiar.
per the rules of your house arrest.

30
00:03:14.653 --> 00:03:17.698
I found it perched
on the Kemper boy's casket.

31
00:03:18.281 --> 00:03:22.452
I thought if I could get it to speak.
maybe I could find out how Connor died.

32
00:03:22.536 --> 00:03:26.540
You won't be able to.
Familiars are bound to their witches.

33
00:03:26.623 --> 00:03:27.791
It'll be dead soon.

34
00:03:27.874 --> 00:03:31.128
The greatest agony it can know
is a life without its master.

35
00:03:31.753 --> 00:03:34.673
Give it here. I'll make it quick.
Hilda can fashion it into a purse.

36
00:03:34.756 --> 00:03:36.842
- No. it's mine. For now.
- [Hilda] Yeah.

37
00:03:36.925 --> 00:03:40.303
I'll. uh. try bribing it with some food.
see if that works.

38
00:03:42.347 --> 00:03:44.266
Would you like a little tomato?

39
00:03:47.936 --> 00:03:49.771
[haunted whispering]

40
00:03:50.272 --> 00:03:51.272
[gasps]

41
00:03:52.023 --> 00:03:53.608
[beast roars]

42
00:03:54.401 --> 00:03:55.861
[snarls]

43
00:03:56.486 --> 00:03:58.613
Hey. you okay?

44
00:03:59.656 --> 00:04:01.074
You're. like. a million miles away.

45
00:04:01.158 --> 00:04:06.705
Yeah. Sorry. I'm fine. I was just having
an out-of-body experience. but I'm back.

46
00:04:07.873 --> 00:04:09.791
[Roz] Great! There you guys are.

47
00:04:09.875 --> 00:04:13.503
You will not believe
the fascism afoot at Baxter High.

48
00:04:13.587 --> 00:04:16.548
So. I go to get my book assignment
approved from Mr. Garland.

49
00:04:16.631 --> 00:04:17.966
and you know what he says?

50
00:04:18.049 --> 00:04:19.885
No. Rejected.

51
00:04:19.968 --> 00:04:22.304
Because my book has been deemed
problematic.

52
00:04:22.387 --> 00:04:24.890
- Wait. but <i>The Bluest Eye</i> is a classic.
- [Roz] Exactly!

53
00:04:24.973 --> 00:04:29.019
No one should get to decide
what we can and can't read.

54
00:04:29.102 --> 00:04:30.102
Agreed.

55
00:04:30.145 --> 00:04:33.440
How can we help. Roz?
No. how can WICCA help?

56
00:04:33.523 --> 00:04:36.443
I mean. that's why our club exists.
[stammers]

57
00:04:36.693 --> 00:04:39.279
We'll take the fight to Hawthorne.
Right. Sabrina?

58
00:04:40.655 --> 00:04:43.992
Um... yeah. [stammers]
Absolutely. if that's what Roz wants.

59
00:04:46.161 --> 00:04:47.245
[sighs] Yeah.

60
00:04:47.954 --> 00:04:48.954
Yeah.

61
00:04:51.875 --> 00:04:55.670
Firstly. let me say very clearly
and for the record.

62
00:04:55.754 --> 00:04:58.590
we do not ban books at Baxter High.

63
00:04:59.716 --> 00:05:02.677
Miss Spellman. have I grown a second head?

64
00:05:03.762 --> 00:05:05.889
No. No. no. no. sir.

65
00:05:05.972 --> 00:05:08.975
Okay. Then why are you looking at me
as if I had?

66
00:05:11.186 --> 00:05:15.398
Principal Hawthorne. why did Mr. Garland
say noto <i>The Bluest Eye.</i>

67
00:05:15.482 --> 00:05:16.775
and call it controversial?

68
00:05:16.858 --> 00:05:21.613
The book that you proposed
has very graphic passages.

69
00:05:21.696 --> 00:05:24.866
I'm certain that Mr. Garland
would've raised the same objections

70
00:05:24.950 --> 00:05:28.870
had you proposed
<i>A Clockwork Orange</i> or<i> Lolita.</i>

71
00:05:28.954 --> 00:05:31.039
So you're saying
those books are banned as well?

72
00:05:31.122 --> 00:05:33.625
I'm saying that this is a public school.

73
00:05:34.042 --> 00:05:37.629
and certain topics and titles

74
00:05:37.838 --> 00:05:41.925
have no place in the hands
of impressionable youths.

75
00:05:42.008 --> 00:05:45.262
<i>♪ I'm a wild. wild woman ♪</i>

76
00:05:46.763 --> 00:05:50.100
- [Roz huffs]
- <i>♪ I'm a wild. wild woman ♪</i>

77
00:05:50.809 --> 00:05:54.896
Wait. Roz. what are you doing?
What exactly are you expecting to find?

78
00:05:54.980 --> 00:05:58.733
I just... I don't believe Hawthorne
for one second.

79
00:05:58.817 --> 00:06:02.821
He may not officially ban books.
but here. Susie. look this up.

80
00:06:02.904 --> 00:06:04.447
Sabrina. see if you can find this one.

81
00:06:04.531 --> 00:06:06.700
<i>♪ I'm the keeper of the treasure ♪</i>

82
00:06:06.783 --> 00:06:09.035
<i>♪ Hunted by every man in sight ♪</i>

83
00:06:09.119 --> 00:06:11.788
<i>♪ I see shadows on the skeletons ♪</i>

84
00:06:11.997 --> 00:06:17.085
<i>♪ Of everything I've done ♪</i>

85
00:06:19.588 --> 00:06:22.215
<i>♪ Ooh ♪</i>

86
00:06:23.216 --> 00:06:24.676
Ms. Curtis. we have a problem.

87
00:06:24.759 --> 00:06:27.721
Uh. this stack of cards.
None of these books are on the shelves.

88
00:06:29.222 --> 00:06:32.392
Yes. I believe these books
have been checked out.

89
00:06:32.934 --> 00:06:34.144
For a while.

90
00:06:34.603 --> 00:06:35.729
What do you mean?

91
00:06:37.272 --> 00:06:40.859
Well. you didn't hear this from me.
but a few years back.

92
00:06:40.942 --> 00:06:45.155
there was a...
a soft purge of bad books.

93
00:06:48.617 --> 00:06:49.701
[door shuts]

94
00:06:50.410 --> 00:06:51.453
Aunt Zelda?

95
00:06:51.536 --> 00:06:55.040
Hilda? You're not gonna believe
what happened at school today.

96
00:06:55.123 --> 00:06:56.708
[Zelda] Oh. we can imagine.

97
00:06:57.250 --> 00:06:58.501
Do you know what this is?

98
00:06:59.753 --> 00:07:03.089
I'll tell you. It's an Infernal Summons.

99
00:07:03.173 --> 00:07:04.007
A what now?

100
00:07:04.090 --> 00:07:08.845
Well. you've been charged
with a rather antiquated offense. dearest.

101
00:07:09.179 --> 00:07:10.096
Breach of Promise.

102
00:07:10.180 --> 00:07:13.475
You made a promise to sign the Dark Lord's
<i>Book of the Beast</i> and then.

103
00:07:13.558 --> 00:07:16.019
when you ran in horror
from your dark baptism.

104
00:07:16.102 --> 00:07:17.187
you broke it.

105
00:07:17.646 --> 00:07:20.482
You humiliated our master
in front of the entire coven.

106
00:07:20.565 --> 00:07:25.362
and now. you will be judged and tried
in front of the entire coven.

107
00:07:26.237 --> 00:07:30.241
Never. in all my years.
has a Spellman been summoned

108
00:07:30.325 --> 00:07:31.409
to the Court of Witches.

109
00:07:31.493 --> 00:07:34.037
I don't understand. Someone is suing me?

110
00:07:34.788 --> 00:07:35.789
The Dark Lord.

111
00:07:36.498 --> 00:07:39.626
[stammers] He's determined
to get you on the Path of Night.

112
00:07:39.709 --> 00:07:42.587
I saw him today. the Dark Lord.

113
00:07:42.671 --> 00:07:46.091
He took possession of Principal Hawthorne
and threatened me.

114
00:07:48.385 --> 00:07:49.803
Did you hear that. sister?

115
00:07:50.387 --> 00:07:52.681
Can you imagine how enraged he must be?

116
00:07:52.764 --> 00:07:55.892
Well. it doesn't matter.
I don't want to be a part of his coven.

117
00:07:55.976 --> 00:07:58.687
I don't want to step foot
in the Academy of Unseen Arts.

118
00:07:58.770 --> 00:08:02.148
and I am certainly not gonna stand trial.

119
00:08:02.232 --> 00:08:05.694
Oh. you most certainly are. Sabrina.
You've been summoned.

120
00:08:05.777 --> 00:08:08.238
And not only you. Hilda and I as well.

121
00:08:10.198 --> 00:08:11.574
We're on trial too.

122
00:08:13.118 --> 00:08:14.828
That doesn't make any sense.

123
00:08:14.911 --> 00:08:17.163
Well. we're your legal guardians. lamb.

124
00:08:17.247 --> 00:08:19.624
So. in the eyes
of the Court of the Witches.

125
00:08:19.708 --> 00:08:21.584
your actions are our actions.

126
00:08:22.002 --> 00:08:24.546
- We're as guilty as you.
- Don't you mean innocent?

127
00:08:24.629 --> 00:08:27.257
- Innocent until proven guilty?
- [Ambrose] That's mortal law.

128
00:08:27.340 --> 00:08:30.677
Witch law is the complete opposite.
Guilty until proven innocent.

129
00:08:30.760 --> 00:08:32.012
Do you know what this is?

130
00:08:33.096 --> 00:08:35.306
It's your Aunt Hilda's tooth.

131
00:08:35.765 --> 00:08:37.726
We have been stripped of our powers.

132
00:08:37.809 --> 00:08:42.605
Which means that we will age and rot.
rapidly. until a verdict is reached.

133
00:08:43.982 --> 00:08:46.693
- [tooth dings]
- Your trial begins at midnight.

134
00:08:49.362 --> 00:08:50.362
[sighs]

135
00:08:54.659 --> 00:08:57.078
I didn't promise the Dark Lord anything.

136
00:08:57.162 --> 00:08:59.164
I didn't sign the <i>Book of the Beast.</i>

137
00:09:00.081 --> 00:09:02.792
And yet. I still have to go to court
and be punished.

138
00:09:02.876 --> 00:09:04.544
Can't I fight this somehow?

139
00:09:04.627 --> 00:09:06.254
[Ambrose] You can. but you'll need help.

140
00:09:06.337 --> 00:09:08.548
Have you ever heard of a man
named Daniel Webster?

141
00:09:09.299 --> 00:09:10.300
I don't think so.

142
00:09:10.383 --> 00:09:13.511
He's a lawyer and occultist
who specializes in witch law.

143
00:09:13.928 --> 00:09:15.472
Total legend.

144
00:09:15.889 --> 00:09:17.766
He's mortal. but. uh...

145
00:09:18.683 --> 00:09:21.686
he's rumored to have once
beaten the Devil himself.

146
00:09:22.103 --> 00:09:23.480
- I'm in.
- Mmm-hmm.

147
00:09:23.563 --> 00:09:25.815
- Where does he live?
- That's the kismet part.

148
00:09:25.899 --> 00:09:28.568
He lives right here. In Greendale.

149
00:09:29.110 --> 00:09:30.278
Willingly?

150
00:09:30.361 --> 00:09:31.696
- Why?
- Don't know.

151
00:09:32.989 --> 00:09:34.157
Bit reclusive. maybe?

152
00:09:35.742 --> 00:09:38.328
[Zelda] You're going to be
the Dark Lord's prosecutor. I imagine.

153
00:09:38.411 --> 00:09:41.790
I don't relish it. but that is
one of my duties as High Priest. yes.

154
00:09:41.873 --> 00:09:46.878
Please. Faustus.
Sabrina made a foolish. impetuous mistake.

155
00:09:47.545 --> 00:09:50.673
Couldn't we settle this between ourselves?

156
00:09:50.757 --> 00:09:52.967
You. me. the Dark Lord...

157
00:09:54.010 --> 00:09:56.971
without the embarrassing spectacle
of a public trial?

158
00:09:57.764 --> 00:10:00.767
The wheels of justice
are already turning. Zelda.

159
00:10:06.481 --> 00:10:07.482
However...

160
00:10:08.149 --> 00:10:11.152
come tonight... with Sabrina...

161
00:10:12.362 --> 00:10:16.116
have her admit her wrongdoing
and beg for forgiveness. immediately.

162
00:10:16.533 --> 00:10:18.368
The Dark Lord is not without mercy.

163
00:10:18.993 --> 00:10:21.830
But he'll require
total submission from the girl.

164
00:10:21.913 --> 00:10:23.164
[Zelda] And he shall have it.

165
00:10:25.208 --> 00:10:26.376
I promise you.

166
00:10:28.169 --> 00:10:29.504
Poor Zelda.

167
00:10:31.589 --> 00:10:34.300
Already. I see
the ravages of age upon you.

168
00:10:35.426 --> 00:10:36.719
[Faustus sighs]

169
00:10:37.303 --> 00:10:39.305
[Zelda breathes deeply]

170
00:10:41.349 --> 00:10:42.600
[Faustus sighs]

171
00:10:49.315 --> 00:10:51.734
Thank you for your time. Faustus.

172
00:10:58.074 --> 00:10:59.242
See you in court.

173
00:11:06.708 --> 00:11:08.376
I don't enjoy being watched.

174
00:11:13.798 --> 00:11:15.925
[Ms. Wardwell] The girl is my charge.

175
00:11:20.555 --> 00:11:23.641
I can't risk leaving her fate in...

176
00:11:24.809 --> 00:11:26.728
lesser hands.

177
00:11:27.812 --> 00:11:29.981
And yet it is your own incompetence

178
00:11:30.148 --> 00:11:32.150
that has brought us to this moment.

179
00:11:33.443 --> 00:11:35.361
[Wardwell laughs]

180
00:11:35.737 --> 00:11:38.072
I eased her to the altar.

181
00:11:38.281 --> 00:11:39.657
as is my way.

182
00:11:39.741 --> 00:11:42.076
A hand on her shoulder.

183
00:11:42.160 --> 00:11:43.703
a whisper in her ear.

184
00:11:44.621 --> 00:11:48.333
But she was at the altar. Blackwood.

185
00:11:48.458 --> 00:11:50.835
You failed to get the signature.

186
00:11:51.044 --> 00:11:53.046
My dear demoness...

187
00:11:54.505 --> 00:11:56.507
your methods are weak.

188
00:11:56.883 --> 00:11:58.468
your will is womanly.

189
00:11:58.593 --> 00:12:00.595
Now I will be the hammer...

190
00:12:01.179 --> 00:12:03.181
that drives this nail home.

191
00:12:03.348 --> 00:12:06.267
As you're blunt. like a hammer.
that's true.

192
00:12:06.351 --> 00:12:10.021
- [Faustus clears throat]
- But don't underestimate her. warlock.

193
00:12:11.231 --> 00:12:13.983
And don't disrespect me.

194
00:12:15.443 --> 00:12:17.445
High Priest or not...

195
00:12:18.905 --> 00:12:20.031
you're still a man.

196
00:12:21.241 --> 00:12:23.243
[Wardwell slurps]

197
00:12:25.245 --> 00:12:26.704
And I feast...

198
00:12:27.997 --> 00:12:30.416
on male flesh.

199
00:12:34.045 --> 00:12:36.214
- [crickets chirring]
- [dog barking in distance]

200
00:12:43.680 --> 00:12:44.889
[door unlocks]

201
00:12:48.142 --> 00:12:49.936
Are you Daniel Webster?

202
00:12:50.895 --> 00:12:51.895
[man] No.

203
00:12:52.981 --> 00:12:54.148
Why? What do you want?

204
00:12:55.275 --> 00:12:57.318
My name is Sabrina Spellman.

205
00:12:58.236 --> 00:12:59.279
Spellman?

206
00:12:59.529 --> 00:13:02.282
And I need a lawyer... to fight the Devil.

207
00:13:04.325 --> 00:13:07.745
I'd offer you a seat. but that would
encourage you to stay. so...

208
00:13:07.829 --> 00:13:10.790
Mr. Webster.
I'm being charged with Breach of Promise.

209
00:13:11.874 --> 00:13:13.418
I ran from my Dark Baptism.

210
00:13:15.837 --> 00:13:17.297
You know what that is. right?

211
00:13:18.339 --> 00:13:19.924
Oh. yeah. I'm familiar.

212
00:13:21.175 --> 00:13:24.053
So what? You. uh. born again?

213
00:13:24.804 --> 00:13:25.888
Renounced Satan?

214
00:13:25.972 --> 00:13:28.933
No. No. I... I'm a half-witch.

215
00:13:31.269 --> 00:13:35.189
They lied and coerced me.
but I didn't sign the <i>Book of the Beast.</i>

216
00:13:35.273 --> 00:13:37.984
And now my family is being punished.

217
00:13:38.401 --> 00:13:41.446
I have to be in court tonight.
in a few hours. and...

218
00:13:42.822 --> 00:13:44.574
and I heard you might be able
to help me.

219
00:13:50.705 --> 00:13:51.705
No.

220
00:13:51.873 --> 00:13:52.873
Sorry.

221
00:13:53.791 --> 00:13:55.168
I don't practice anymore.

222
00:13:56.711 --> 00:13:58.046
[pouring drink]

223
00:13:58.338 --> 00:14:00.131
Breach of Promise. that's tricky.

224
00:14:07.388 --> 00:14:08.723
Well. good luck to you.

225
00:14:08.973 --> 00:14:10.058
[slams door]

226
00:14:37.668 --> 00:14:39.587
Hell and damnation.

227
00:14:41.339 --> 00:14:43.341
[owl hoots]

228
00:14:50.139 --> 00:14:51.349
Hey. these are good. Harv.

229
00:14:51.808 --> 00:14:53.684
I mean. they're messed up.

230
00:14:54.936 --> 00:14:56.521
You're a twisted little weirdo.

231
00:14:57.146 --> 00:14:58.146
Thanks. Tommy.

232
00:14:58.606 --> 00:15:00.233
[both chuckle]

233
00:15:01.567 --> 00:15:03.528
I showed them to the guy
that runs the bookstore.

234
00:15:03.778 --> 00:15:05.988
The vampire guy. you mean?

235
00:15:06.531 --> 00:15:08.658
[chuckles] Dr. Cerberus. yeah.

236
00:15:09.033 --> 00:15:11.202
He said I could do some posters
for his store.

237
00:15:11.828 --> 00:15:13.871
Maybe even work there weekends.
if I wanted.

238
00:15:14.080 --> 00:15:15.623
That your idea of a joke?

239
00:15:16.165 --> 00:15:18.334
You want to hang out
in the back of a comic book shop

240
00:15:18.418 --> 00:15:20.294
with some pervert who plays dress-up?

241
00:15:20.503 --> 00:15:22.004
Dad. jeez. relax.

242
00:15:22.505 --> 00:15:24.132
You want a job. Harvey?

243
00:15:24.507 --> 00:15:27.135
I've got a job for you. In the mines.

244
00:15:27.427 --> 00:15:30.387
- You'll start with a shift this week.
- Dad. we can manage fine without...

245
00:15:30.638 --> 00:15:31.681
You heard him. Tom.

246
00:15:32.265 --> 00:15:35.726
Your brother's ready to work.
and I'm giving him work. End of story.

247
00:15:42.233 --> 00:15:43.401
[Zelda sighs deeply]

248
00:15:43.651 --> 00:15:45.653
[owl hoots]

249
00:15:47.363 --> 00:15:48.406
[Zelda] Remember. ladies.

250
00:15:48.489 --> 00:15:51.617
we carry ourselves
with aplomb and dignity.

251
00:15:51.701 --> 00:15:54.537
We admit our wrongs.
accept our punishment.

252
00:15:54.871 --> 00:15:57.540
and try to put this whole sordid mess
behind us.

253
00:15:57.623 --> 00:15:59.709
- Isn't that right. Sabrina?
- [thunder rumbling]

254
00:15:59.876 --> 00:16:01.252
Do I have a choice?

255
00:16:01.335 --> 00:16:02.587
Not really. no.

256
00:16:02.879 --> 00:16:04.672
[bell tolling]

257
00:16:10.303 --> 00:16:12.555
We. the profane...

258
00:16:13.514 --> 00:16:16.017
gather here tonight
in this sacrilegious Court

259
00:16:16.100 --> 00:16:17.852
to serve the Dark Lord's justice.

260
00:16:18.561 --> 00:16:21.647
A deplorable crime has been committed
against our master and savior.

261
00:16:21.731 --> 00:16:24.525
- [crowd] Hail Satan! Praise him!
- [Hilda mumbles] Praise Satan.

262
00:16:24.609 --> 00:16:29.238
Sabrina Spellman stands accused
before The Infernal Three.

263
00:16:29.572 --> 00:16:35.620
guilty of breaking her promise.
her pledge. to the Dark Lord.

264
00:16:36.120 --> 00:16:41.250
[low. distorted voices]
Sabrina Spellman. stand.

265
00:16:46.547 --> 00:16:48.633
[Faustus]
When the accused is confirmed guilty.

266
00:16:48.716 --> 00:16:53.221
not only will she abandon
her mortal life immediately.

267
00:16:53.554 --> 00:16:59.393
but. upon her death.
she shall burn for 333 years in the Pit.

268
00:16:59.477 --> 00:17:01.312
as his pleasure demands.

269
00:17:01.395 --> 00:17:03.314
- [crowd applauding]
- [gavel banging]

270
00:17:06.192 --> 00:17:09.403
Accused. how plead you?

271
00:17:09.820 --> 00:17:12.073
I... I...

272
00:17:13.199 --> 00:17:15.201
[door opens]

273
00:17:16.285 --> 00:17:18.287
She pleads not guilty.

274
00:17:18.454 --> 00:17:20.665
[people murmuring]

275
00:17:21.666 --> 00:17:22.708
[door closes]

276
00:17:22.792 --> 00:17:24.043
[gavel banging]

277
00:17:25.711 --> 00:17:26.796
Mr. Webster.

278
00:17:28.047 --> 00:17:29.047
[laughs]

279
00:17:30.675 --> 00:17:35.471
You are not unknown to this court.
but you are unwelcome. sir. and uninvited.

280
00:17:35.555 --> 00:17:36.764
[Webster] Untrue. sir.

281
00:17:38.140 --> 00:17:42.645
- Where my client goes... I follow.
- [Zelda] Client?

282
00:17:44.063 --> 00:17:47.733
- Sabrina?
- He's my lawyer. Aunt Zelda.

283
00:17:48.192 --> 00:17:50.152
[people murmuring]

284
00:17:51.737 --> 00:17:53.337
[Zelda]
As if things weren't dire enough.

285
00:17:53.406 --> 00:17:57.493
you go and hire this mortal pettifogger
behind our backs.

286
00:17:57.577 --> 00:18:01.622
With all due respect. madam.
I am well-versed in witch law.

287
00:18:01.706 --> 00:18:04.292
Oh. I know exactly who you are.
Mr. Webster.

288
00:18:04.959 --> 00:18:08.004
I remember you sniffing around my brother
years ago.

289
00:18:08.379 --> 00:18:10.172
A hanger-on. a dilettante.

290
00:18:10.256 --> 00:18:12.466
Wait. You knew my father?

291
00:18:13.384 --> 00:18:15.219
He's the reason I came to Greendale.

292
00:18:16.178 --> 00:18:18.514
Your father taught me witch law...

293
00:18:19.557 --> 00:18:21.517
offered me comfort when there was none.

294
00:18:21.892 --> 00:18:22.977
He helped me out.

295
00:18:24.520 --> 00:18:25.980
I'd like to return the favor.

296
00:18:26.063 --> 00:18:27.732
[bell tolling]

297
00:18:29.859 --> 00:18:33.863
Do you know what Breach of Promise means.
Miss Spellman?

298
00:18:33.946 --> 00:18:37.158
It's when you make a promise.
and then break it.

299
00:18:37.700 --> 00:18:40.661
Which I. categorically. did not do.

300
00:18:40.745 --> 00:18:41.996
It is most commonly invoked

301
00:18:42.079 --> 00:18:45.249
when a groom runs out on a bride
he's promised to wed.

302
00:18:45.333 --> 00:18:47.043
I only mention that. because... [scoffs]

303
00:18:47.126 --> 00:18:50.338
...well. were you and the Dark Lord
not courting

304
00:18:50.421 --> 00:18:52.506
in advance of your Dark Baptism?

305
00:18:53.341 --> 00:18:55.509
"Courting"? In what way?

306
00:18:55.593 --> 00:18:58.137
Did you not willingly go into the woods
that night?

307
00:18:58.721 --> 00:19:01.891
Wearing. of all things. a wedding dress?

308
00:19:01.974 --> 00:19:03.351
[people murmuring]

309
00:19:03.434 --> 00:19:05.078
[Faustus]
Fact is. you gave every indication

310
00:19:05.102 --> 00:19:07.521
that it was your intention
to fulfill a promise made.

311
00:19:07.605 --> 00:19:09.982
You showed up for a ceremony
you'd committed to

312
00:19:10.066 --> 00:19:13.361
and then. at the moment
of consummation. you fled.

313
00:19:16.030 --> 00:19:17.323
You broke your promise.

314
00:19:20.701 --> 00:19:21.701
That's all.

315
00:19:22.411 --> 00:19:23.411
[man] Guilty!

316
00:19:24.372 --> 00:19:26.874
- [woman] Tramp!
- [people murmuring]

317
00:19:30.127 --> 00:19:33.506
Sabrina. members of the court.

318
00:19:33.589 --> 00:19:35.883
where is the tangible proof?

319
00:19:36.300 --> 00:19:40.221
If this baptism is to be considered
a wedding.

320
00:19:40.304 --> 00:19:42.306
where is the marriage license?

321
00:19:42.890 --> 00:19:45.518
The blood tests
this great township demands?

322
00:19:46.060 --> 00:19:47.812
Show me the signatures!

323
00:19:48.604 --> 00:19:50.523
Hell. show me the groom!

324
00:19:50.606 --> 00:19:52.483
[crowd murmuring]

325
00:19:53.567 --> 00:19:54.567
No contract.

326
00:19:55.152 --> 00:19:56.278
No promise.

327
00:19:57.738 --> 00:19:58.656
No case.

328
00:19:58.739 --> 00:20:00.741
[low gasps. murmurs]

329
00:20:01.450 --> 00:20:02.576
Your Dishonors...

330
00:20:03.619 --> 00:20:07.790
I'd like to submit into evidence
our most unholy grimoire.

331
00:20:08.416 --> 00:20:09.667
the <i>Book of the Beast.</i>

332
00:20:11.293 --> 00:20:15.131
Miss Spellman. would you be so kind
as to open it to the page I've indicated?

333
00:20:20.970 --> 00:20:25.725
Would you please read the name
that's been written... there?

334
00:20:26.851 --> 00:20:28.269
Nice and loud. child.

335
00:20:28.352 --> 00:20:31.355
It says. "Sabrina Spellman."

336
00:20:32.064 --> 00:20:33.607
- But...
- [people murmuring]

337
00:20:34.108 --> 00:20:35.568
[Sabrina] I don't understand this.

338
00:20:35.651 --> 00:20:37.820
This is dated
only a few days after I was...

339
00:20:37.903 --> 00:20:43.951
Your Dishonors. are we to believe that
a baby signed the <i>Book of the Beast</i>

340
00:20:44.034 --> 00:20:45.703
three days after she was born?

341
00:20:45.786 --> 00:20:49.331
This is obviously a fraud.
a blatant forgery.

342
00:20:49.415 --> 00:20:51.542
I call to the stand Zelda Phiona Spellman.

343
00:20:51.917 --> 00:20:53.919
[people murmuring]

344
00:20:54.044 --> 00:20:55.713
[woman in crowd] What? Impossible!

345
00:20:58.382 --> 00:21:00.426
Aunt Zelda. what's happening?

346
00:21:07.224 --> 00:21:09.351
Ms. Spellman. Zelda.

347
00:21:10.936 --> 00:21:14.148
Take us back to this date written here.

348
00:21:17.568 --> 00:21:19.361
[Zelda] Of course. Your Excellency.

349
00:21:20.529 --> 00:21:21.529
I...

350
00:21:22.531 --> 00:21:25.951
I accompanied my brother
into the Greendale Wood.

351
00:21:27.244 --> 00:21:33.000
In his arms. he carried
his newborn daughter... Sabrina.

352
00:21:34.001 --> 00:21:39.256
When we reached a clearing.
he placed the babe on an altar. and...

353
00:21:41.050 --> 00:21:42.718
signed her name
in the <i>Book of the Beast.</i>

354
00:21:42.802 --> 00:21:44.553
[people murmuring]

355
00:21:45.387 --> 00:21:47.264
Promising her soul to the Dark Lord.

356
00:21:47.973 --> 00:21:49.350
[people applauding]

357
00:21:49.433 --> 00:21:50.434
What?

358
00:21:53.395 --> 00:21:54.814
[Sabrina] <i>Now it makes sense!</i>

359
00:21:54.897 --> 00:21:57.942
All your strong-arming trying
to get me to sign.

360
00:21:58.025 --> 00:21:59.735
You were just trying to cover up the fact

361
00:21:59.819 --> 00:22:03.113
that you had already pawned me off
to the Dark Lord like a used car.

362
00:22:03.197 --> 00:22:05.324
You were never meant to find out.

363
00:22:05.908 --> 00:22:08.494
You were meant to choose the Path of Night

364
00:22:08.577 --> 00:22:10.704
and sign your name willingly. That way...

365
00:22:10.788 --> 00:22:15.793
That way. I never would've found out
about my father's betrayal and yours?

366
00:22:17.920 --> 00:22:19.505
[Zelda] Edward needed a witness.

367
00:22:20.047 --> 00:22:22.424
Why would he do that to me?

368
00:22:25.344 --> 00:22:27.388
A certain bargain had been struck.

369
00:22:27.471 --> 00:22:32.017
and the price your father paid for it
was your name in that book.

370
00:22:32.268 --> 00:22:33.853
What could've been worth it?

371
00:22:36.355 --> 00:22:38.065
Permission to marry your mother.

372
00:22:38.315 --> 00:22:40.860
The Dark Lord granted it in exchange for...

373
00:22:40.943 --> 00:22:43.404
For me... his daughter.

374
00:22:44.029 --> 00:22:48.200
And you stood there.
and you watched him do it. Aunt Zelda!

375
00:22:48.284 --> 00:22:50.160
You helped him do it!

376
00:22:57.710 --> 00:22:58.710
[Webster slurps]

377
00:23:02.256 --> 00:23:03.507
[girl's voice echoing] Daddy?

378
00:23:05.342 --> 00:23:07.469
Why did you let me die. Daddy?

379
00:23:08.095 --> 00:23:10.139
It hurt so much.

380
00:23:10.222 --> 00:23:11.222
Stop.

381
00:23:11.891 --> 00:23:15.603
You should be spending your time
getting ready to join me down here. Daddy.

382
00:23:17.104 --> 00:23:21.108
Not defending a useless.
backwoods. half-breed witch.

383
00:23:24.862 --> 00:23:28.240
Tick-tock. Daniel Webster.

384
00:23:29.450 --> 00:23:32.077
Tick-tock.

385
00:23:32.995 --> 00:23:35.372
Tick-tock.

386
00:23:36.332 --> 00:23:38.876
Tick-tock.

387
00:23:55.059 --> 00:23:56.477
Caffeine not kicking in yet?

388
00:23:57.186 --> 00:23:58.604
I didn't sleep very well.

389
00:23:59.146 --> 00:24:01.482
My Aunt Zelda and I
got into a fight. and...

390
00:24:03.192 --> 00:24:06.070
Is it okay if we don't talk about it?
I'm sorry.

391
00:24:06.487 --> 00:24:07.529
[Harvey] Of course.

392
00:24:09.531 --> 00:24:11.784
I got into it with my old man
last night. too.

393
00:24:13.577 --> 00:24:17.831
[exhales] He's. uh...
making me start work at the mines.

394
00:24:18.332 --> 00:24:21.752
What? Why? You hate the mines.

395
00:24:21.835 --> 00:24:24.630
I don't just... [sighs]
...hate them. Sabrina. I...

396
00:24:25.089 --> 00:24:26.173
What? What?

397
00:24:28.258 --> 00:24:29.258
What is it?

398
00:24:30.177 --> 00:24:31.177
[sighs]

399
00:24:33.472 --> 00:24:36.642
Eight years ago.
I was playing hide-and-seek

400
00:24:37.101 --> 00:24:39.103
with Tommy and a couple of his buddies.

401
00:24:40.020 --> 00:24:44.149
<i>And I. like an idiot.
decided to go hide in the mines.</i>

402
00:24:45.901 --> 00:24:47.987
<i>And I'm in there. alone.</i>

403
00:24:49.238 --> 00:24:52.825
<i>Half-an-hour goes by. and then an hour...</i>

404
00:24:54.159 --> 00:24:55.577
<i>and no one finds me.</i>

405
00:24:56.870 --> 00:24:59.248
<i>And I'm trying to get back
to the mine entrance.</i>

406
00:25:02.376 --> 00:25:03.419
And then I...

407
00:25:05.838 --> 00:25:06.922
[exhales]

408
00:25:07.047 --> 00:25:08.882
And then I saw it. Sabrina.

409
00:25:10.300 --> 00:25:11.300
What?

410
00:25:11.802 --> 00:25:14.013
It's gonna sound crazy.
but I swear to God it...

411
00:25:14.096 --> 00:25:15.514
[roars]

412
00:25:16.098 --> 00:25:17.349
It looked like a goat.

413
00:25:17.933 --> 00:25:21.395
Only bigger. and standing upright
on its hind legs. and it...

414
00:25:21.979 --> 00:25:25.232
it smelled like a...
a book of matches had been struck.

415
00:25:25.816 --> 00:25:26.816
Brimstone.

416
00:25:27.317 --> 00:25:28.610
And it terrified me.

417
00:25:29.236 --> 00:25:31.697
<i>I couldn't move. I couldn't breathe.</i>

418
00:25:32.406 --> 00:25:33.657
<i>I started to cry.</i>

419
00:25:34.867 --> 00:25:35.867
[sighs deeply]

420
00:25:36.368 --> 00:25:39.204
I was still crying when Tommy found me
five hours later.

421
00:25:41.331 --> 00:25:42.458
It's been years.

422
00:25:42.750 --> 00:25:44.460
No one else has seen the goat guy.

423
00:25:46.378 --> 00:25:47.671
But I keep thinking...

424
00:25:48.630 --> 00:25:50.716
Sabrina. what if it's still down there...

425
00:25:51.592 --> 00:25:52.718
waiting for me?

426
00:25:53.802 --> 00:25:55.054
[school bell rings]

427
00:25:55.137 --> 00:25:57.139
[pop song playing]

428
00:25:58.515 --> 00:26:02.478
[girl] Take one. It's required reading.
There you go. Here. take it.

429
00:26:03.729 --> 00:26:06.774
- You'll never guess. Sabrina.
- What's happening. Ms. Wardwell?

430
00:26:06.857 --> 00:26:10.611
Well. the young ladies of W-I-C-C-A.
that's WICCA to you. Mr. Kinkle.

431
00:26:11.445 --> 00:26:12.988
are making their voices heard.

432
00:26:13.614 --> 00:26:15.074
[Susie] Thank you. Thank you.

433
00:26:15.157 --> 00:26:21.121
Here's a list of books
Baxter High doesn't want you to read!

434
00:26:21.330 --> 00:26:24.917
And they also happen to be
great works of literature.

435
00:26:25.000 --> 00:26:26.710
You guys. when did you do this?

436
00:26:26.794 --> 00:26:29.838
- Last night.
- I mean. they're just books. you know.

437
00:26:29.922 --> 00:26:33.092
What are people so afraid of?
That Principal Hawthorne's gonna...

438
00:26:34.885 --> 00:26:35.928
[Roz clears throat]

439
00:26:36.261 --> 00:26:39.306
Ladies. about your claims.

440
00:26:39.389 --> 00:26:43.018
You can't punish someone for handing out
flyers. Principal Hawthorne.

441
00:26:43.102 --> 00:26:45.270
On the contrary. Miss Spellman.

442
00:26:45.354 --> 00:26:50.651
I just wanted Miss Walker to know
that I called the PTA and the school board

443
00:26:50.734 --> 00:26:52.778
about <i>The Bluest Eye.</i>

444
00:26:53.028 --> 00:26:54.780
They are reviewing the matter.

445
00:26:54.863 --> 00:26:57.574
and will come back to me tomorrow
with their thoughts.

446
00:26:59.243 --> 00:27:01.662
You're welcome. Miss Walker.

447
00:27:14.091 --> 00:27:16.385
- [low murmurs]
- [opera music plays softly]

448
00:27:45.581 --> 00:27:46.861
[Ambrose] Did you know him well?

449
00:27:47.541 --> 00:27:48.541
Connor?

450
00:27:49.418 --> 00:27:50.919
We dated a few times. but...

451
00:27:51.545 --> 00:27:52.963
I'm sorry for your loss.

452
00:27:55.048 --> 00:27:57.718
- My name's Ambrose. by the way.
- Luke.

453
00:27:58.427 --> 00:27:59.427
I. uh...

454
00:27:59.803 --> 00:28:01.763
I'm just gonna miss him. that's all.

455
00:28:03.056 --> 00:28:04.766
Him and that stupid lizard of his.

456
00:28:06.977 --> 00:28:08.770
- He took it everywhere.
- Hmm.

457
00:28:09.104 --> 00:28:10.522
Yeah. or it followed him.

458
00:28:10.606 --> 00:28:11.607
[chuckles]

459
00:28:11.940 --> 00:28:13.817
They never stray far. do they?

460
00:28:15.569 --> 00:28:20.365
Are you saying you're familiar...
with iguanas like that?

461
00:28:22.618 --> 00:28:25.120
I'm saying that I know Connor was very...

462
00:28:25.662 --> 00:28:26.662
attached to it.

463
00:28:27.539 --> 00:28:30.334
- They had a bond.
- Because I have him.

464
00:28:31.126 --> 00:28:32.127
Upstairs.

465
00:28:33.337 --> 00:28:34.421
In my room.

466
00:28:36.506 --> 00:28:38.592
If you wanted to say hi.

467
00:28:40.010 --> 00:28:42.471
[woman sniffs and cries]

468
00:28:46.642 --> 00:28:47.643
I should go.

469
00:28:48.227 --> 00:28:51.230
But... another time maybe.

470
00:28:56.235 --> 00:28:58.237
[Wardwell humming]

471
00:29:01.448 --> 00:29:03.325
[teacher] <i>By the autumn of 1805.</i>

472
00:29:03.408 --> 00:29:07.287
the men of the Lewis and Clark Expedition
were starving. desperate.

473
00:29:07.371 --> 00:29:08.580
and running out of time.

474
00:29:08.664 --> 00:29:11.250
Just before them
lay the Continental Divide.

475
00:29:11.333 --> 00:29:13.126
<i>and just beyond that...</i>

476
00:29:13.210 --> 00:29:16.338
- [teacher's voice fades]
- [humming continues]

477
00:30:42.174 --> 00:30:43.342
[slams book]

478
00:30:51.141 --> 00:30:52.517
[Sabrina] Why are you helping me?

479
00:30:52.851 --> 00:30:57.064
What do you want out of this.
Defender of the Damned?

480
00:30:57.189 --> 00:30:58.189
Oh.

481
00:30:59.149 --> 00:31:00.525
Okay. So you know.

482
00:31:00.609 --> 00:31:05.113
The people you've helped set free.
murderers and monsters.

483
00:31:05.197 --> 00:31:07.157
The kinds of crimes they've committed.

484
00:31:07.240 --> 00:31:11.036
- Everyone's entitled to a defense.
- Not you. You're fired.

485
00:31:11.787 --> 00:31:13.705
Wait! Sabrina. stop.

486
00:31:15.374 --> 00:31:19.211
I've been where you are right now.
trapped by the Devil.

487
00:31:19.961 --> 00:31:23.298
I made a deal. a long time ago.

488
00:31:23.548 --> 00:31:26.635
to be the greatest lawyer in the world.

489
00:31:28.178 --> 00:31:29.805
I was young and ambitious.

490
00:31:30.347 --> 00:31:32.641
And I signed my name away.

491
00:31:32.808 --> 00:31:33.850
A different book...

492
00:31:34.810 --> 00:31:35.852
but the same beast.

493
00:31:37.521 --> 00:31:40.357
And what do you know?
I started winning cases.

494
00:31:41.358 --> 00:31:45.737
And by the time I realized the only cases
I got were the most depraved.

495
00:31:45.821 --> 00:31:49.324
the most obscene. it was too late.

496
00:31:49.783 --> 00:31:53.537
And that was his little trick. you see.
And there's always a trick.

497
00:31:55.872 --> 00:31:56.915
And a price.

498
00:32:01.086 --> 00:32:02.712
I set a man free...

499
00:32:03.380 --> 00:32:07.509
who had done unspeakable things
to a number of women.

500
00:32:09.219 --> 00:32:10.929
And after I freed him.

501
00:32:11.555 --> 00:32:14.141
when I wasn't home. he broke in...

502
00:32:17.018 --> 00:32:18.520
and he did those things...

503
00:32:19.688 --> 00:32:20.688
to my daughter.

504
00:32:21.565 --> 00:32:22.565
Oh. no.

505
00:32:22.691 --> 00:32:27.654
Now I know that I have done
more than my share of bad in the past.

506
00:32:30.782 --> 00:32:35.328
But I think...
that I might be able to save you.

507
00:32:36.997 --> 00:32:38.123
If you'll let me.

508
00:32:38.874 --> 00:32:40.041
It's a long shot...

509
00:32:41.418 --> 00:32:42.502
but maybe.

510
00:32:44.713 --> 00:32:46.715
[bell tolling]

511
00:32:50.302 --> 00:32:54.681
Ms. Spellman. both you and your sister
are certified midwives.

512
00:32:54.764 --> 00:32:55.932
- Yes.
- Yes.

513
00:32:56.683 --> 00:33:00.187
You have delivered many babies
in the witch community.

514
00:33:00.270 --> 00:33:02.522
including your own niece. Sabrina.

515
00:33:02.856 --> 00:33:03.690
- Yes.
- Yes.

516
00:33:03.773 --> 00:33:05.901
Can you verify for the court. then...

517
00:33:06.860 --> 00:33:09.905
was Sabrina born of mortal woman?

518
00:33:09.988 --> 00:33:11.907
- She was. yes.
- Absolutely. yes.

519
00:33:12.115 --> 00:33:16.912
Making her half-witch.
half-mortal and. therefore.

520
00:33:16.995 --> 00:33:19.706
only half-subject
to the laws of this court!

521
00:33:19.789 --> 00:33:21.875
This is absurd. Your Dishonors.

522
00:33:21.958 --> 00:33:24.044
No. sir. it is her right!

523
00:33:24.544 --> 00:33:27.047
I demand a jury of mortals!

524
00:33:27.130 --> 00:33:30.342
- [people murmuring]
- [Webster] And a change of venue!

525
00:33:30.425 --> 00:33:33.470
I reject the authority of this court
over my client!

526
00:33:33.803 --> 00:33:37.015
- [gavel banging]
- Disorder in the court!

527
00:33:38.058 --> 00:33:41.311
- [knocking on window]
- [music playing indistinctly]

528
00:33:46.525 --> 00:33:47.984
[knocking continues]

529
00:33:54.783 --> 00:33:57.619
- "Psst! Open the window. Mark."
- Judas Priest!

530
00:33:59.454 --> 00:34:00.454
Luke.

531
00:34:03.083 --> 00:34:04.209
How did you get in here?

532
00:34:04.292 --> 00:34:07.295
You invited me earlier. remember?

533
00:34:07.921 --> 00:34:10.966
- So what. you're a vampire?
- No. I'm a warlock.

534
00:34:11.466 --> 00:34:13.301
Like Connor was. Like you are.

535
00:34:15.929 --> 00:34:16.929
Aren't you?

536
00:34:29.401 --> 00:34:30.735
[Faustus] <i>The prosecution</i>

537
00:34:30.819 --> 00:34:34.030
and witching community are familiar
with human law. Mr. Webster.

538
00:34:34.614 --> 00:34:38.535
If Sabrina's true. dominant nature
is to be determined mortal or witch.

539
00:34:38.618 --> 00:34:39.661
so be it.

540
00:34:39.744 --> 00:34:42.122
We shall invoke human laws to test her.

541
00:34:42.372 --> 00:34:43.975
- That is not what I was suggesting.
- One:

542
00:34:43.999 --> 00:34:46.293
We may subject Sabrina to trial by water.

543
00:34:46.376 --> 00:34:49.212
She will be bound
and dropped into the river.

544
00:34:49.296 --> 00:34:51.381
- If she floats. she's a witch.
- [people applauding]

545
00:34:51.756 --> 00:34:54.843
If she drowns. she's human.
And free to go.

546
00:34:54.926 --> 00:34:56.553
- Unacceptable!
- [Faustus] Or two:

547
00:34:57.387 --> 00:35:00.098
The accused will submit
to being stripped and examined.

548
00:35:00.181 --> 00:35:03.560
in full view of the coven.
for a witch's mark upon her body.

549
00:35:03.643 --> 00:35:07.856
Should a mark be identified.
this trial continues. uninterrupted.

550
00:35:07.939 --> 00:35:09.774
Should no mark be found.

551
00:35:10.150 --> 00:35:13.945
this court will be forced to recognize
her so-called "humanity."

552
00:35:15.905 --> 00:35:16.905
[woman] Yes!

553
00:35:18.283 --> 00:35:20.160
Absolutely not. I forbid it!

554
00:35:20.243 --> 00:35:22.912
Sit down. Zelda. before you collapse.
You're skin and bone.

555
00:35:22.996 --> 00:35:24.789
Sabrina. I have to ask.

556
00:35:25.165 --> 00:35:27.876
Do you even know if you have a mark?

557
00:35:27.959 --> 00:35:29.669
- [door opens]
- Let's start there.

558
00:35:30.128 --> 00:35:32.005
[Faustus]
Perhaps there's another way.

559
00:35:35.216 --> 00:35:39.387
You'll excuse my unannounced visitation.
but I come bearing felicitous tidings.

560
00:35:39.638 --> 00:35:41.931
I've pleaded on your behalf
to the Dark Lord.

561
00:35:42.015 --> 00:35:45.435
and he has offered a path

562
00:35:45.935 --> 00:35:47.646
- through this thicket.
- [sighs]

563
00:35:47.979 --> 00:35:49.064
Praise Satan!

564
00:35:49.481 --> 00:35:52.108
The Dark Lord will waive
your punishment in the Pit.

565
00:35:52.192 --> 00:35:55.779
He will even allow you yearly visitations
with your mortal friends.

566
00:35:55.862 --> 00:36:00.200
but... you must ratify your signature
in the <i>Book of the Beast.</i>

567
00:36:00.283 --> 00:36:02.327
and you must withdraw from Baxter High.

568
00:36:02.410 --> 00:36:06.414
and begin your studies
at the Academy of Unseen Arts immediately.

569
00:36:06.915 --> 00:36:08.833
But this is perfect! Sabrina!

570
00:36:09.167 --> 00:36:12.045
[Faustus] We'll await your answer
tomorrow night in court.

571
00:36:12.295 --> 00:36:13.295
Ladies.

572
00:36:14.130 --> 00:36:15.130
Sir.

573
00:36:18.343 --> 00:36:21.012
[door opens and closes]

574
00:36:24.224 --> 00:36:26.434
We will not take this deal.

575
00:36:26.518 --> 00:36:30.522
But the Dark Lord has been moved
by our plight to show mercy.

576
00:36:31.189 --> 00:36:35.527
- Do you know how rare that is?
- She's right. So think about that.

577
00:36:36.111 --> 00:36:39.739
Why offer a deal? It's a trick.

578
00:36:39.823 --> 00:36:41.533
Remember whom you're dealing with!

579
00:36:48.289 --> 00:36:49.749
[Salem meows]

580
00:36:50.458 --> 00:36:54.671
[alarm clock imitates maniacal laughter]

581
00:37:01.469 --> 00:37:02.595
[sighs deeply]

582
00:37:08.226 --> 00:37:09.436
[Ambrose chuckles]

583
00:37:10.812 --> 00:37:11.812
Uh-huh.

584
00:37:12.480 --> 00:37:14.858
[grunts. sighs]

585
00:37:15.859 --> 00:37:17.569
Still got it. Spellman.

586
00:37:27.954 --> 00:37:29.205
[flies buzzing]

587
00:37:30.206 --> 00:37:33.168
[Ambrose] I guess you couldn't live
without Connor. little one.

588
00:37:38.047 --> 00:37:40.550
- What are you smiling at?
- What? Nothing.

589
00:37:41.050 --> 00:37:43.052
It's just... [chuckles]

590
00:37:43.636 --> 00:37:46.723
You get this look on your face
when you're thinking stuff over...

591
00:37:47.474 --> 00:37:50.310
and I always wonder what it is.
because you look so serious.

592
00:37:50.977 --> 00:37:53.229
Harvey. can I talk to you
about something...

593
00:37:56.024 --> 00:37:57.609
that is serious?

594
00:37:58.651 --> 00:37:59.651
Always.

595
00:37:59.694 --> 00:38:02.405
I... have to ask you for a favor.

596
00:38:02.489 --> 00:38:04.991
and it's gonna sound crazy...

597
00:38:05.784 --> 00:38:07.202
but it's important.

598
00:38:08.411 --> 00:38:09.537
I can do crazy.

599
00:38:10.163 --> 00:38:11.163
And important.

600
00:38:14.918 --> 00:38:16.169
[Sabrina sighs]

601
00:38:20.548 --> 00:38:22.550
My aunts say
every Spellman has a birthmark.

602
00:38:22.634 --> 00:38:25.470
but I can't find one
and I have to be sure.

603
00:38:25.553 --> 00:38:26.721
one way or the other.

604
00:38:30.099 --> 00:38:31.099
[sighs]

605
00:38:36.064 --> 00:38:37.064
Will you look?

606
00:38:38.316 --> 00:38:39.316
For a birthmark?

607
00:38:40.777 --> 00:38:46.282
- I'm so confused right now.
- Me too. I'm super confused about. well...

608
00:38:47.951 --> 00:38:49.410
everything. except you.

609
00:38:49.994 --> 00:38:51.996
- I'm not confused about you.
- Me neither.

610
00:38:52.080 --> 00:38:55.333
Because I love you.
and I trust you to do the right thing.

611
00:38:55.416 --> 00:38:56.709
and to tell me the truth.

612
00:38:56.793 --> 00:38:59.671
In fact. I trust you more than I do
anyone else right now.

613
00:39:17.272 --> 00:39:18.273
[chuckles]

614
00:39:24.946 --> 00:39:26.322
[Harvey sighs]

615
00:39:26.823 --> 00:39:27.823
Fair is fair. right?

616
00:39:42.130 --> 00:39:43.339
[Harvey exhales softly]

617
00:40:01.733 --> 00:40:03.151
Before you keep looking...

618
00:40:16.456 --> 00:40:17.498
[Sabrina] Hey.

619
00:40:21.169 --> 00:40:22.169
What's wrong?

620
00:40:22.879 --> 00:40:25.214
We got called
into Principal Hawthorne's office

621
00:40:25.298 --> 00:40:27.508
because he had some news
about the book banning...

622
00:40:27.592 --> 00:40:29.385
The PTA said they'd hold
a town hall meeting.

623
00:40:29.719 --> 00:40:33.640
where we could present our case
to the school board. In three months.

624
00:40:35.767 --> 00:40:39.604
Okay. well. three weeks. three months.

625
00:40:39.687 --> 00:40:43.024
even if it takes three whole years. Roz.
we're gonna make them understand.

626
00:40:43.107 --> 00:40:44.525
That's what I said. Yeah.

627
00:40:44.776 --> 00:40:47.236
[trembling voice] Yeah. Yeah. no.

628
00:40:47.320 --> 00:40:48.696
[chuckles] I know.

629
00:40:49.697 --> 00:40:51.199
Three months is not that long.

630
00:40:51.783 --> 00:40:53.201
Roz. what's going on?

631
00:41:01.918 --> 00:41:03.795
[Roz] I'm sorry. [sniffs]

632
00:41:04.170 --> 00:41:06.464
I'm always trying to do what my dad said.

633
00:41:07.298 --> 00:41:10.134
"Pray and face it bravely."

634
00:41:11.386 --> 00:41:13.179
That's his solution for everything.

635
00:41:14.931 --> 00:41:16.891
But prayer's not gonna stop it.

636
00:41:17.433 --> 00:41:18.434
Stop what?

637
00:41:21.646 --> 00:41:22.646
[sniffles]

638
00:41:25.775 --> 00:41:27.527
Myopic atrophy.

639
00:41:30.571 --> 00:41:32.824
Dr. Spector says that. uh...

640
00:41:34.117 --> 00:41:35.618
in about three months...

641
00:41:37.245 --> 00:41:38.454
maybe less.

642
00:41:38.997 --> 00:41:42.875
the ugliest. thickest glasses
in the world aren't gonna stop me

643
00:41:42.959 --> 00:41:44.877
from going totally blind.

644
00:41:49.132 --> 00:41:50.132
[scoffs]

645
00:41:51.217 --> 00:41:54.637
You know. I even counted how many books...

646
00:41:55.263 --> 00:41:59.142
I could realistically read
before it's too late.

647
00:42:00.435 --> 00:42:04.480
That's why every single one is important.

648
00:42:18.494 --> 00:42:21.039
[Tommy] It's a short shift.
Couple hours' hard work.

649
00:42:21.414 --> 00:42:23.624
back up topside
with some dirt on your face.

650
00:42:24.167 --> 00:42:25.418
It'll shut Dad up.

651
00:42:26.169 --> 00:42:28.755
You'll be on my crew. and I promise.

652
00:42:28.838 --> 00:42:31.007
I won't let you outta my... sight.

653
00:42:31.799 --> 00:42:32.799
Harv?

654
00:42:38.056 --> 00:42:39.182
[voice echoes] Harvey?

655
00:42:40.266 --> 00:42:41.266
Harv?

656
00:42:42.101 --> 00:42:43.603
- [beast roars]
- [Tommy] It's okay.

657
00:42:43.686 --> 00:42:47.231
- [breathing heavily]
- Just... take a breath.

658
00:42:49.567 --> 00:42:52.612
Tommy... I can't.

659
00:42:53.154 --> 00:42:54.947
- It's okay. It's okay.
- I can't. I just...

660
00:42:56.157 --> 00:42:57.157
I know.

661
00:42:58.618 --> 00:42:59.702
I remember.

662
00:43:00.787 --> 00:43:03.206
Look. for today. why don't you head home?

663
00:43:03.915 --> 00:43:05.083
We'll try again later.

664
00:43:06.459 --> 00:43:09.087
- But Dad said...
- I'll see you at the house when I'm done.

665
00:43:11.172 --> 00:43:13.633
It's okay. Harv. I promise.

666
00:43:25.478 --> 00:43:28.731
[Sabrina] Aunties. Mr. Webster.
I've made my decision.

667
00:43:32.151 --> 00:43:36.197
I'm not taking the deal.
I'll submit to Blackwood's exam.

668
00:43:37.115 --> 00:43:39.867
I don't have a witch's mark.
so there's nothing to lose.

669
00:43:39.951 --> 00:43:41.035
Except your dignity.

670
00:43:42.120 --> 00:43:44.914
- Aunt Zelda.
- Back into the fray. then. eh. cousin?

671
00:43:46.082 --> 00:43:49.502
When they find out I don't have a mark.
Mr. Webster. what happens then?

672
00:43:49.585 --> 00:43:50.920
We demand a retrial...

673
00:43:52.630 --> 00:43:56.300
in human court.
where you're innocent until proven guilty.

674
00:43:56.384 --> 00:43:59.387
And we demand that my aunties' powers
and youth are restored.

675
00:43:59.470 --> 00:44:00.972
It's non-negotiable.

676
00:44:01.055 --> 00:44:05.893
Thank you for that. sweetheart.
but to be stripped and pawed...

677
00:44:05.977 --> 00:44:07.562
I've had worse done to me.

678
00:44:09.230 --> 00:44:12.400
Besides. there are a lot of people facing
their fears right now.

679
00:44:12.483 --> 00:44:15.069
fighting battles they know
they're not gonna win.

680
00:44:15.153 --> 00:44:18.656
So. if this is mine. well.
then let's get it over with.

681
00:44:20.324 --> 00:44:22.869
But no tricks. no plea bargains.

682
00:44:26.455 --> 00:44:28.124
We should go. I'll be outside.

683
00:44:34.672 --> 00:44:35.506
[dish clatters]

684
00:44:35.590 --> 00:44:38.176
It keeps getting worse and worse for her.

685
00:44:39.886 --> 00:44:42.263
- Where do you think you're going?
- [Hilda] Upstairs.

686
00:44:42.346 --> 00:44:45.349
[groans]
Don't follow me. Don't wait for me.

687
00:44:45.433 --> 00:44:47.018
Just get her to the court.

688
00:44:47.852 --> 00:44:50.563
You're not the only one with secrets.
Zelda Spellman.

689
00:45:22.970 --> 00:45:23.970
[Harvey sighs]

690
00:45:24.430 --> 00:45:26.724
- [front door opens. slams]
- [Mr. Kinkle] Harvey!

691
00:45:29.143 --> 00:45:30.143
Harvey!

692
00:45:30.853 --> 00:45:32.772
Boy. when I tell you to do something.

693
00:45:32.855 --> 00:45:34.815
- you do it!
- Hey. Dad. get the hell off me!

694
00:45:34.899 --> 00:45:37.193
- Dad. stop it!
- [both panting]

695
00:45:39.070 --> 00:45:40.446
You better watch yourself.

696
00:45:40.863 --> 00:45:42.823
And you. you're gonna get
in that damn mine.

697
00:45:42.907 --> 00:45:44.325
and work an honest-to-God shift.

698
00:45:45.076 --> 00:45:47.578
- He's gonna start pulling his weight.
- I'll get more guys.

699
00:45:48.162 --> 00:45:51.749
Push comes to shove. I'll take his shifts.
but Harvey's done. Dad.

700
00:45:52.375 --> 00:45:54.627
I'm not gonna let him
waste his life like...

701
00:46:11.894 --> 00:46:15.982
Sabrina. am I to understand
that you come now before this court

702
00:46:16.065 --> 00:46:18.109
to endure the test of the witch's mark.

703
00:46:18.192 --> 00:46:21.696
as described and demanded
by your mortal laws?

704
00:46:23.698 --> 00:46:25.658
Yes. Father Blackwood.

705
00:46:26.242 --> 00:46:29.370
We request the examination be held
in closed chambers.

706
00:46:29.453 --> 00:46:30.579
- Denied.
- [Hilda] Stop.

707
00:46:31.539 --> 00:46:32.539
Stop! Stop!

708
00:46:38.754 --> 00:46:43.175
If this is some feeble attempt to delay
the agreed-upon course of action...

709
00:46:43.259 --> 00:46:44.259
You're sure?

710
00:46:45.636 --> 00:46:48.806
Your Dishonors. I call Hildegard
Antoinette Spellman to the stand!

711
00:46:48.889 --> 00:46:51.434
[Faustus] This is unacceptable!
The test is about to begin!

712
00:46:51.517 --> 00:46:56.230
- I demand that...
- Hilda Spellman. approach us.

713
00:47:01.944 --> 00:47:04.280
I have new evidence
to submit to the court.

714
00:47:06.198 --> 00:47:11.162
Ms. Spellman. please read
the name printed here on this document.

715
00:47:11.412 --> 00:47:14.165
[clears throat]
Yes. It reads. um. "Sabrina Spellman."

716
00:47:14.457 --> 00:47:16.250
Witnessed by...

717
00:47:16.334 --> 00:47:19.545
[Hilda]
Witnessed by her mother. Diana Spellman...

718
00:47:20.046 --> 00:47:23.382
and. well. me. Hilda Spellman.

719
00:47:25.760 --> 00:47:29.513
I offer in evidence
a baptismal certificate...

720
00:47:30.306 --> 00:47:32.725
from the Holy Mother Church of Greendale.

721
00:47:32.850 --> 00:47:34.518
[people murmuring]

722
00:47:39.732 --> 00:47:42.902
Your Dishonors.
if this certificate is authentic...

723
00:47:43.694 --> 00:47:47.573
it would seem we have competing claims
upon the soul of Sabrina Spellman.

724
00:47:47.656 --> 00:47:51.452
No. sir. what we have
is a binding contract.

725
00:47:51.535 --> 00:47:53.329
witnessed by her mother...

726
00:47:54.205 --> 00:47:59.168
notarized and dated
one day before Edward Spellman inscribed

727
00:47:59.251 --> 00:48:01.587
his daughter's name
in the <i>Book of the Beast...</i>

728
00:48:02.213 --> 00:48:04.757
thereby rendering
the aforementioned inscription...

729
00:48:05.549 --> 00:48:11.472
the agreed-upon promise.
null and void. QED!

730
00:48:11.555 --> 00:48:13.557
[people murmuring]

731
00:48:18.562 --> 00:48:22.066
These last-minute theatrics
make a mockery of this court!

732
00:48:22.566 --> 00:48:27.196
This... is spurious. this is outrageous!

733
00:48:27.279 --> 00:48:31.117
No. I'll tell you what's outrageous.
Father Blackwood.

734
00:48:31.951 --> 00:48:33.744
- The Dark Lord's behavior!
- [crowd murmurs]

735
00:48:44.380 --> 00:48:45.464
[Webster] Well. now.

736
00:48:45.965 --> 00:48:49.343
I'd say you just forced the Devil
to the bargaining table.

737
00:48:51.720 --> 00:48:55.891
And I've been summoned
to the court's private chambers.

738
00:49:26.881 --> 00:49:28.132
[Zelda] <i>How could you. Hilda?</i>

739
00:49:28.799 --> 00:49:30.926
How's it any different
to your secret with Edward?

740
00:49:31.010 --> 00:49:33.554
It's completely different! And appalling!

741
00:49:34.180 --> 00:49:35.389
A Christian church?

742
00:49:35.473 --> 00:49:37.516
Have you no shame? Have you no pride?

743
00:49:37.600 --> 00:49:41.187
So. Dad didn't know
that Mom had me baptized?

744
00:49:41.270 --> 00:49:42.313
In secret?

745
00:49:43.606 --> 00:49:46.567
- Why?
- [Hilda] She said not to tell him.

746
00:49:46.650 --> 00:49:50.070
I just assumed
it was Diana being sentimental.

747
00:49:50.362 --> 00:49:52.990
Perhaps she suspected
what Edward had planned.

748
00:49:54.325 --> 00:49:56.327
- So they were both deceivers.
- [Zelda] Sabrina!

749
00:49:56.785 --> 00:49:58.329
Honor Thy Father and Mother!

750
00:49:59.455 --> 00:50:01.457
[thunder rumbling]

751
00:50:01.540 --> 00:50:03.584
No more secrets. Aunties.

752
00:50:04.585 --> 00:50:05.711
Do you understand?

753
00:50:06.587 --> 00:50:09.256
No more lying to me about my own family...

754
00:50:10.257 --> 00:50:11.842
ever again.

755
00:50:12.968 --> 00:50:14.595
[bell tolling]

756
00:50:22.811 --> 00:50:26.982
Due to conflicts of contract.
baptism. and breeding.

757
00:50:27.608 --> 00:50:31.487
the Hellbound Court of Greendale decrees
that Sabrina Spellman...

758
00:50:32.988 --> 00:50:34.865
shall retain her mortal life...

759
00:50:35.115 --> 00:50:37.117
[people murmuring]

760
00:50:37.451 --> 00:50:42.331
...on the condition that she also attend
the Academy of Unseen Arts...

761
00:50:43.165 --> 00:50:45.334
as well as weekly Black Mass.

762
00:50:48.128 --> 00:50:50.214
Think of it as dual-citizenship.

763
00:50:54.301 --> 00:50:55.344
Your Dishonors...

764
00:50:57.221 --> 00:50:58.264
I accept.

765
00:50:59.974 --> 00:51:00.974
So be it.

766
00:51:01.642 --> 00:51:03.644
This court is adjourned to the shadows.

767
00:51:04.186 --> 00:51:07.022
Full powers are restored
to the Spellman family.

768
00:51:07.231 --> 00:51:09.149
[thunder crashes]

769
00:51:12.236 --> 00:51:15.155
Praise Satan! I'm young again!

770
00:51:25.791 --> 00:51:28.627
[thunder rumbles]

771
00:51:31.338 --> 00:51:32.548
[Sabrina] Mr. Webster?

772
00:51:35.426 --> 00:51:37.678
Won't you come over to our house
to celebrate?

773
00:51:39.096 --> 00:51:41.724
It's late and I'm old.

774
00:51:42.558 --> 00:51:43.559
Another time.

775
00:51:45.311 --> 00:51:48.272
Well... thank you.

776
00:51:50.316 --> 00:51:51.525
For helping me win.

777
00:52:00.659 --> 00:52:01.785
Some advice.

778
00:52:02.995 --> 00:52:06.290
Take advantage of this qualified victory.

779
00:52:06.707 --> 00:52:10.628
Learn everything you can
about your adversary.

780
00:52:10.711 --> 00:52:13.589
And fight... for what's yours.

781
00:52:16.842 --> 00:52:18.594
Nobody's ever beaten the Devil...

782
00:52:20.429 --> 00:52:21.555
but you just might.

783
00:52:21.972 --> 00:52:23.974
[thunder rumbles]

784
00:52:39.281 --> 00:52:41.283
[phone rings]

785
00:52:43.702 --> 00:52:44.702
[door creaks open]

786
00:52:45.704 --> 00:52:47.414
That was Father Blackwood calling.

787
00:52:48.874 --> 00:52:54.046
It seems. Hilda. that you've been
excommunicated from the Church of Night.

788
00:52:55.297 --> 00:52:57.174
[sputters] What?

789
00:52:58.425 --> 00:52:59.259
[Hilda stammers]

790
00:52:59.343 --> 00:53:02.096
- They can't do that. can they?
- They most certainly can.

791
00:53:02.638 --> 00:53:03.638
And should.

792
00:53:04.848 --> 00:53:07.476
You took part in a Catholic baptism.

793
00:53:08.852 --> 00:53:11.730
You've cast doubt on our devotion
to the Church of Night.

794
00:53:11.814 --> 00:53:14.608
And our Dark Lord is a vengeful lord.

795
00:53:16.568 --> 00:53:17.569
[soft whimper]

796
00:53:17.861 --> 00:53:19.571
What do I do now. then?

797
00:53:20.989 --> 00:53:21.989
Sister?

798
00:53:23.867 --> 00:53:26.328
Be grateful excommunication
is all that's being done to you.

799
00:53:44.221 --> 00:53:45.806
Did you come to congratulate me?

800
00:53:46.432 --> 00:53:47.433
[Wardwell clicks tongue]

801
00:53:48.016 --> 00:53:49.016
No.

802
00:53:49.893 --> 00:53:51.562
And congratulate you on what?

803
00:53:52.563 --> 00:53:54.648
A half-victory is no victory at all.

804
00:53:54.732 --> 00:53:57.401
I delivered on my promise
to get her into the academy.

805
00:53:59.903 --> 00:54:03.115
And now that she's under my watch
and authority...

806
00:54:04.408 --> 00:54:05.951
I'll bend her to my will.

807
00:54:06.618 --> 00:54:08.245
- Or break her.
- [Wardwell] Hmm.

808
00:54:08.328 --> 00:54:11.457
It's always brute force with you men.
isn't it?

809
00:54:15.335 --> 00:54:16.545
But real corruption...

810
00:54:17.421 --> 00:54:20.257
is a thin. subtle blade.

811
00:54:21.383 --> 00:54:22.468
Sabrina's strength.

812
00:54:22.968 --> 00:54:28.098
the bonds that must be severed.
are those to the mortals around her.

813
00:54:30.559 --> 00:54:32.060
[softly] The people she loves.

814
00:54:32.811 --> 00:54:36.607
<i>But not to worry.
I'm quite good at tearing souls apart.</i>

815
00:54:36.940 --> 00:54:39.860
<i>One piece at a time.</i>

816
00:54:42.613 --> 00:54:44.698
[gasps. breathes heavily]

817
00:54:45.574 --> 00:54:48.202
There you are!
We've been looking all over for you!

818
00:54:48.535 --> 00:54:49.535
Come with me.

819
00:54:55.834 --> 00:54:57.419
What is this? [chuckles softly]

820
00:55:00.422 --> 00:55:01.548
What's going on?

821
00:55:01.632 --> 00:55:03.342
[Wardwell] Sabrina. Rosalind.

822
00:55:03.592 --> 00:55:07.137
Welcome to Baxter High's new.
secret book club.

823
00:55:07.846 --> 00:55:10.182
Sponsored by W-I-C-C-A.

824
00:55:10.432 --> 00:55:12.851
Banned titles only.

825
00:55:13.393 --> 00:55:15.312
With you leading the group. of course.

826
00:55:19.399 --> 00:55:20.692
[Wardwell] Aw! [chuckles]

827
00:55:21.485 --> 00:55:23.070
I'm so proud of you girls.

828
00:55:23.654 --> 00:55:28.200
We're gonna have such great fun
reading all those juicy.

829
00:55:28.283 --> 00:55:30.911
forbidden novels that
they don't want us to.

830
00:55:32.037 --> 00:55:33.455
I've got quite a list.

831
00:55:34.832 --> 00:55:36.959
A little something for each of you.

832
00:55:40.921 --> 00:55:41.921
[Roz chuckles]

833
00:55:46.510 --> 00:55:48.428
[theme music playing]

834
00:56:46.570 --> 00:56:47.988
[man] <i>Brett. move your head.</i>

835
00:56:48.305 --> 00:57:48.340
